title.narrative: % of pregnant women and caregivers of children less than 2 years who participated in counselling sessions within the last 3 mths in target villages

actual.value: 2016:10% (10,000 pregnant women and 30,000 caregivers of children less than 2 years) in Mbeya, Iringa and Njombe.

title.narrative: % of health facilities (dispensaries & health facilities) with at least 1 Health worker trained on infant and young child feeding counselling

actual.value: 2016:40% of health facilities with at least one health worker trained on IYCF in Mbeya, Iringa and Njombe.

title.narrative: % of children under 5 years with SAM treated

actual.value: 2016:45% of SAM caseload treated in UN supported areas (Zanzibar, Mbeya, Iringa and Njombe regions).

title.narrative: of communities with capacities to provide IYCF counselling service.

actual.value: 2016:As of mid year 420 communities have CHWs trained and equipped to provide IYCF.

title.narrative: % of districts with Vit A supplementation coverage above 90%

actual.value: 2016:80% of districts in Mainland and 80% of districts in Zanzibar with Vitamin A supplementation coverage above 90%.

title.narrative: % of targeted regions and districts with at least one nutrition officer

baseline.value: No nutrition officers at regional level

target.value: 2016:100% of regions and targeted districts have one trained nutrition coordinator

actual.value: 2016:90% of regions and 90% of districts appointed nutrition officers. 87% of district and 60% of regional nutrition officers trained in Mainland and 100% of nutrition focal persons trained in Zanzibar.
